         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers1598">
               <p>Charity, daughter of <persName>Thomas</persName> and <persName>Margaret
                     Goodhew</persName> of <placeName>London</placeName>, was christened in <date
                     when="1689-04">Apr. 1689</date>. On <date when="1718-12-04">Dec. 4, 1718</date>
                  she married <persName><ref target="/persons/pers1605.xml"/>Vincent
                     Perronet</persName>. While she did not share her husband&apos;s strong support
                  of Methodism that blossomed in <date when="1746">1746</date>, partly through the
                  death of their son <persName>Vincent</persName> (<date from="1724" to="1746"
                     >1724–46</date>) from smallpox, she was ever the faithful host to the Wesley
                  brothers and their preachers. When Charity died on <date when="1763-02">Feb.
                     1763</date>, <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName> made
                  a special trip to <placeName>Shoreham</placeName> to preside at her funeral. See
                  Batty, <hi rend="italic">Perronet</hi>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
